libbc-hrbl (1.1.0-1) stable; urgency=medium

  * Path grammar: quoted segments in bc_hrbl_reader_find. Segments wrapped
    in single (') or double (") quotes are treated as literal keys, so
    paths containing dots or brackets can now be looked up via the reader
    find API and the bc-hrbl query CLI (e.g. files.'src/main.c'.digest).
    No escape sequences; the segment ends at the next matching quote.

 -- Younes Benmoussa <younes.benmoussa@pm.me>  Thu, 23 Apr 2026 19:00:00 +0000

libbc-hrbl (1.0.0-1) stable; urgency=medium

  * Initial public release.
  * Binary format: little-endian `.hrbl`, magic `HRBL`, 128-byte header
    with xxh3_64 checksum, 32-byte footer with duplicate checksum and
    file_size for truncation detection, root index and block entries
    sorted by xxh3_64 with unique keys per scope.
  * Reader: zero-copy mmap, path-style lookup `a.b[0].c`, typed
    getters, block and array iterators.
  * Writer: flat append-only builder with begin/end scopes, parallel
    finalise (configurable worker count).
  * Verify: buffer and file entry points, magic / version / header /
    footer / ordering / UTF-8 / checksum checks.
  * Export: one-way pretty JSON output via `bc_hrbl_export_json`.
  * Full sanitizer coverage (asan / tsan / ubsan / memcheck) and
    cppcheck-clean sources.

 -- Younes Benmoussa <younes.benmoussa@pm.me>  Thu, 23 Apr 2026 14:00:00 +0000
